Operations on List
----------------------------

    1. Creating a new list

            ArrayList list1 = new ArrayList();
            LinkedList list1 = new LinkedList();

            List list = new ArrayList();
            List list = new LinkedList();

            List<Integer> numslist = new ArrayList<>()
            List<String> namesList = new LinkedList<>()

    2. Basic operations: adding, retrieving, updating, removing elements

        a. adding the element on the list
                boolean add(Object obj)
                void add(int index, Object obj)
                boolean addAll(Collection c)

        b. Retrieve the element of a list
                Object get(int index)
                    - returns the object at the specified index

        c. Updating elements
                Object set(int index, Object element)

             - the set(index, element) method is used to replace the element at the specified index
                by the specified element.

        d. removing the elements from a list
                    boolean remove(int index)
                    boolean remove(Object obj)
